# Named Podman volume backing the curated Flathub mirror.
#
# svk-flathub-sync.py writes to it directly (natively on the host, not from a
# container — see that script's docstring for why); flathub-mirror-serve.
# container mounts the SAME volume read-only to serve it over HTTP. Quadlet
# names the underlying Podman volume "systemd-<unit-stem>", i.e.
# "systemd-flathub-mirror" here — svk-flathub-sync.py resolves that name via
# `podman volume inspect` to get the real on-disk path.

[Volume]
